# preFlight WASM/Emscripten compatibility patch
# Originally translated from allanwrench28/orcaslicer-wasm; significantly
# extended for preflight's diverged GCode pipeline and post-export config dump.
#
# Apply against a clean preflight checkout:
#   cd preflight && git apply path/to/preflight-wasm.patch
#
# Coverage (27 modified files):
#
#   Build-system gating (Emscripten/TBB/optional deps):
#     CMakeLists.txt, src/CMakeLists.txt,
#     bundled_deps/hidapi/CMakeLists.txt,
#     src/libslic3r/CMakeLists.txt
#
#   Pipeline rewrites — the original parallel_pipeline used tbb::filter<I,O>
#   type erasure that the wasm_shims TBB stub does not provide. Both
#   process_layers variants are driven by a hand-rolled sequential loop
#   under __EMSCRIPTEN__:
#     src/libslic3r/GCode.cpp                (2 process_layers paths)
#
#   Post-export workaround (NEW vs. the original orcaslicer-wasm port) —
#   skip append_full_config() under __EMSCRIPTEN__. The cfg.keys() virtual
#   dispatch on Print::m_full_print_config traps with "null function" under
#   -sEMULATE_FUNCTION_POINTER_CASTS=1 + -fexceptions, before entering the
#   function body. The config-comment block it would emit is purely
#   informational, so skipping is benign:
#     src/libslic3r/GCode.cpp                (append_full_config call site)
#
#   Source-level guards — CGAL/Qhull/Boost.Process/libpng/seqarrange disabled,
#   replacement nop bodies, transitive-include additions, Eigen 3.4 cast<>()
#   hoists, libcxx unique_ptr {} ambiguity workaround:
#     src/libslic3r/AABBTreeLines.hpp
#     src/libslic3r/Feature/FuzzySkin/FuzzySkin.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Feature/Interlocking/InterlockingGenerator.{cpp,hpp}
#     src/libslic3r/Format/STEP.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/GCode.hpp
#     src/libslic3r/GCode/PostProcessor.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Geometry/VoronoiUtilsCgal.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/LayerRegion.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Model.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/ObjectID.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/PNGReadWrite.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Platform.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Print.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/PrintObject.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/ProgressConfig.hpp
#     src/libslic3r/ShortestPath.hpp
#     src/libslic3r/SupportSpotsGenerator.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/SurfaceCollection.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Thread.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/TriangleMesh.cpp
#     src/libslic3r/Utils/DirectoriesUtils.cpp
#
# The corresponding bridge code lives outside this patch, in the
# preflight-wasm/bridge/ sibling tree. Key things it does:
#   - passes GCodeProcessorResult* to do_export() so the in-memory G-code
#     (gcode_result.gcode_object->text_buffer()) is returned to JS — preflight's
#     do_export uses memory-based G-code processing and does NOT write a file
#     when no result pointer is supplied
#   - global operator new/delete overrides DISABLED (#if 0) — keeping them
#     interferes with libcxxabi's exception machinery under
#     -sEMULATE_FUNCTION_POINTER_CASTS=1 and surfaces as null-function traps
#     at G-code finalization.
#
